headline: DTE Energy's Hallelujah for Heat returns to Detroit, Oct. 25
summary: DTE Energy today announced the return of Hallelujah for Heat on Saturday, Oct. 25, at Fellowship Chapel (7707 Outer Dr., Detroit). Doors open at 6 p.m., with performances starting at 7 p.m., featuring Pastor John P. Kee and the New Life Community Choir, and an opening set by Jeremiah Towner and the Highest Praise Choir.
